{"search_data": "JharkhandJharkhand Paddy Procurement Scheme to Purchase Dhaan at MSP from Farmers Jharkhand govt. to start Dhaan Adhiprapti Yojana from 1st December 2018 to 31 March 2019 to procure paddy at the rate of Rs. 1750/quintal from farmers, tokens to be given to farmers through SMS or phone calls to sell crops at procurement centers \u0939\u093f\u0902\u0926\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092a\u0922\u093c\u0947\u0902Jharkhand Paddy Procurement Scheme to Purchase Paddy from FarmersThe state govt. of Jharkhand has fixed a target to procure 4 lakh metric tonne of paddy from farmers. The Paddy Procurement Scheme (Dhaan Adhiprapti Yojana) will start from 1 December 2018 and will end on 31 March 2019. Till date, there are 239 paddy procurement centers in the state and the numbers of these centers can be increased by the concerned department if needed.Farmers will get Rs. 1750 for one quintal of paddy as per the MSP fixed by the Modi government. The payment of paddy will go directly into the bank accounts of the farmers through NEFT / RTGS or DBT modes. Bonus is being under consideration and the concerned department is going to submit the report on expenses incurred for bonus. After consideration of this report, the final decision on bonus would be taken.All the farmers would get information regarding selling of their paddy through SMS or mobile phones. Farmers can then contact the paddy procurement centers to get the token and date to sell their dhaan. Moreover, all those farmers who have not obtained token will again get SMS on their mobile phones to sell their crops in a sequence wise manner. Under Santhal Pargana division, the state govt. will procure paddy through decentralized system in districts Godda, Deoghar, Dumka, Jamtara, Sahibganj and Pakur.\u090f\u0915 \u0926\u093f\u0938\u0902\u092c\u0930 \u0938\u0947 \u0928\u094d\u092f\u0942\u0928\u0924\u092e \u0938\u092e\u0930\u094d\u0925\u0928 \u092e\u0942\u0932\u094d\u092f \u092a\u0930 \u0930\u093e\u091c\u094d\u092f \u0938\u0930\u0915\u093e\u0930 239 \u0915\u0947\u0902\u0926\u094d\u0930\u094b\u0902 \u092a\u0930 \u0927\u093e\u0928 \u0916\u0930\u0940\u0926\u0947\u0917\u0940\u0964 \u0905\u0928\u094d\u0928\u0926\u093e\u0924\u093e \u0915\u093f\u0938\u093e\u0928\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u094b \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0924\u093f \u0915\u094d\u0935\u093f\u0902\u091f\u0932 1750 \u0930\u0941\u092a\u092f\u0947 \u0938\u092e\u0930\u094d\u0925\u0928 \u092e\u0942\u0932\u094d\u092f \u0915\u093e \u092d\u0941\u0917\u0924\u093e\u0928 \u0915\u093f\u092f\u093e \u091c\u093e\u090f\u0917\u093e\u0964 #AgriSummit2018 pic.twitter.com/ByBpqQE9XP\u2014 Raghubar Das (@dasraghubar) November 28, 2018In Palamu division (Palamu, Garhwa, Latehar), the state govt. has choosen the FCI as the nodal agency for procurement. In North Chotanagpur division (Chatra, Hazaribagh, Koderma, Giridih, Ramgarh, Bokaro, Dhanbad), South Chotanagpur division (Lohardaga, Gumla, Simdega, Ranchi, Khunti), Kolhan division (West Singhbhum, Saraikela Kharsawan, East Singhbhum) and Santhal Pargana division (Godda, Deoghar, Dumka, Jamtara, Sahibganj and Pakur), procurement would be done through Jharkhand State Food and Civil Supplies Corporation Ltd.The state govt. has allocated a fund of Rs. 200 crore for paddy procurement (dhaan adhiprapti) which was previously reserved for sugar procurement. All the farmers will get prices of their paddy within 15 days after selling their crops at the procurement centers.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}